node.text:
We’re launching a Tuesday TIP OF THE WEEK series to help answer some commonly asked questions from our community! Today we’re kicking off with our friend @takebetterphotosofyourdog 📸 

Every dog deserves a great portrait. But it’s not always possible to hire a professional photographer, and most people don’t own a DSLR or mirrorless camera. Luckily, cell phones come with pretty good built-in cameras these days!

Watch this video for a list of tips that'll help you be a better photographer - with your cell phone! Be sure to ready our blog (LINK IN BIO) or download the guide on www.dogphototips.com 

We’ll focus one week a month on how to take better photos of your dog, so leave your questions in the comments and tune back in next month for the answers! 

Check out more tips from Take Better Photos of Your Dog: @takebetterphotosofyourdog
Cover photo: @marshygsp

By now, you've probably heard how CBD can be beneficial for both humans and pets alike. For those new to the conversation, CBD is a derived from hemp or cannabis and does not contain THC, which is the substance that produces a high for its users. 

In 2018, a Cornell study reported 80% of osteoarthritis dogs who used CBD showed “significant improvement in pain levels and quality of life”. 

In a world where too many pets are homeless, abandoned, or returned, CBD seems to offer a ray of hope. The potential to steady a dog’s nerves long enough to charm a family, relieve a joint pain, aid in separation anxiety, or help behave when meeting new people could make all the difference in a pet’s life. Incorporating CBD into a consistent routine is one practice that can support this transition and pave the way for calm, happy families. 

Link in bio to read more about how CBD can help animals or donate a CBD product to a shelter pet through @welovecuddly! 

#dogsofinstagram #cbdforpets #cbdhealth #theanxiouspet #releasethepeace #relaxandroll @theanxiouspet
